@node Description "What is it used for?"

 Description
 ~~~~~~~~~~~
 PbView is a phonebook viewer for NComm v2.0 & v3.0. It is based on the
 PbViewer included with the NComm v2.0 archive, but has a intuitionised
 display of all the data held in the phone book.

 PbView will allow you to view the entries in your .phone file without
 having to load in NComm. It can be particularly useful if your serial
 port is in use by another program and you want to check the details of
 a particular BBS.

@endnode

@Node Use "How it works"

 PbView can be run under both WB1.3 & 2.04, and can be started from either 
 Workbench or CLI.

 The program runs from CLI as follows:

 PbView [phonebook]

 Where phonebook is the name and path of the phonebook you wish to view. If
 phonebook is omitted, or the program is started from Workbench a file
 requester will be displayed.

 The requester is produced with reqtools, and requires reqtools.library to
 be in your LIBS: directory. If for any reason PbView is unable to open
 reqtools.library it will open the default phonebook (NComm:NComm.phone),
 or exit if that file can not be found.

 The program is controlled entirely by the 8 gadgets in the lower righthand
 corner.

 The left & right gadgets move backwards and forwards through the entries
 in the file one at a time.

 The Jump to Start [ |< ] and Jump to End [ >| ] gadgets will jump to the
 first and last entries respectively.

 The Search Gadget will bring up a window allowing you to enter a BBS name
 (or part of a name) to be searched for. The program will then start 
 searching from the first entry until it reaches a match.

 The Next gadget will search for the next entry that matches the name
 entered in the Search window.

 The about gadget will open a small window giving information about the
 program, and the quit gadget will exit the program (suprise suprise)
@endnode

@node History "History of PbView"

 Changes:

 v1.2	 06.09.94 - Added in Username, Dial Cmd & In Menu? output.
 v1.1	 04.09.94 - Finally got round to adding in NComm 3 specific baud
		    and protocol values.
 v1.0	 19.09.92 - Added in Search routine and Jump to Start/End gadgets.
 v0.9	 23.08.92 - Rewrote code to read entire phone list in one go.
 v0.8	 11.07.92 - Added in file requesters.
 v0.7	 25.06.92 - Fixed bug in WB1.3 gadget code.
 v0.6	 21.06.92 - Improved WB1.3 window output.
 v0.5	 14.06.92 - Added in WB1.3 window code.
 v0.4	 13.06.92 - First release.

 ALL VERSIONS BELOW v0.4 were internal Alpha test versions.

 Future enhancements:

 Filter system to allow filtering of boards by Baud Rate etc.
@endnode


